prepareForEcoRoute(25.10)                            prepareForEcoRoute(25.10)

Name
       prepareForEcoRoute  - Converts special nets to geometrically equivalent
       regular nets

Syntax
       prepareForEcoRoute

       [-help]

       [-exclude <net*>]

       [-ignore_wire_status]

       [-nets <net*>]

       Converts special nets to geometrically equivalent regular nets. You can
       convert all special nets, named special nets, or all special  nets  ex-
       cept those you specify. The prepareForEcoRoute command supports polygon
       shapes as well.

       Notes

              * If  you  do not specify any parameters, the prepareForEcoRoute
                command converts all routed special nets to signal nets.

              * Use the prepareForEcoRoute command to convert  physical  nets.
                To convert logical nets, use setNet.

              * The prepareForEcoRoute command does not work for PG nets.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each prepareForEcoRoute parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man prepareForEcoRoute

       -exclude <net*>
              Specifies  the special nets that you do not want to convert. You
              can use wildcards.

              * If a name contains a special character, enclose it  in  braces
                ({}).

              * If you specify multiple net names, enclose the names in braces
                ({}).

       -ignore_wire_status
              Converts  all special wires and vias, irrespective of their sta-
              tus.

       -nets <net*>
              Specifies the special nets to be converted. You  can  use  wild-
              cards.

              * If  a  name contains a special character, enclose it in braces
                ({}).

              * If you specify multiple net names, enclose the names in braces
                ({}).

       Note: For backward compatibility, this command also supports  the  fol-
       lowing syntax for nets to convert:

       prepareForEcoRoute <netName> [<netName2 netName3> ...]

Examples
              * The following command converts special nets named clk* to reg-
                ular nets:

                prepareForEcoRoute -nets clk*

              * The  following command converts all special nets, except those
                named clk1*, to regular nets:

                prepareForEcoRoute -exclude clk1*

              * The following command converts special nets named clk* to reg-
                ular nets, except nets named clk1*:

                prepareForEcoRoute -nets clk* -exclude clk1*

              * The following command converts all special  nets  named  clk*,
                a2, and s2[1], except for nets clk1 and clk2, to regular nets:

                prepareForEcoRoute -nets {clk* a2 s2[1]} -exclude {clk1 clk2}

